node.text:
You hear people talk about wanting to become successful all the time.
.
They want to make more money.
.
They want to lose weight and get ready for summer.
.
And they want to quit their job and become their own boss.
.
But at the end of the day, what do they do?
.
They spend their time drinking and partying...
.
Watching Netflix all day...
.
And scrolling through social media envying all the successful people
..
That's why they never achieve the success they want... 'cause they never learn how to hunt.
.
I teach all my students how to hunt with a high income skill. They can take the same skill and travel to anywhere, anytime, with anyone and make a living.
.
If you want to learn how to hunt for success with a high income skill, DM me now.
.
And I know you’re different, so let me hear your commitment…
.
Give me a “I’m willing to hunt!” in the comments below.

node.text:
Success is NOT about waiting around, thinking positively, and then hopefully one day you’ll get it.

It’s about doing whatever it takes.

It’s about practicing it till you become it.

And it’s about ignoring the haters and following your heart.

How can you do that?

Ask yourself, “What would the successful version of me do?”

The habits… the decisions… the way you think… the words you say… the people you hang out with.

Write everything down on a piece of paper and then do that.

Even if you don’t know how.

Even if it scares you.

And even if you don’t have the right skills or knowledge, you learn them.

If you’re going to do what the successful version of you would do, put “I will be successful” in the comments.

node.text:
I know you might see opportunities online that could be perfect for you. 
 
But you don’t have the financial resources right now. 
 
What I’ve found in myself and my mentees, is… 
 
It’s the people that are the most resourceful that get the furthest in life. 
 
So, don’t just give up because you don't have the money. 
 
Find a way to get it. 
 
Exhaust all your options. 
 
Sell some old clothes or things around the house on eBay. 
 
Find free things online you can resell. 
 
See if you can find someone to lend you money. 
 
I know if you get creative you’ll find a way to make your dreams a reality. 
 
Comment below different ways you can be resourceful.
